div.div: Comedy, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life

The second season of Hataraku Maou-sama! MgRonald’s best demon lord worker is back, climbing the corporate ladder to become ruler of Earth. But Maou’s plans of domination might need to be put on hold when a small girl claims to be his and Emi’s child! (Source: Crunchyroll)
Comedy, Psychological, Romance, Slice of Life, Supernatural

Wracked by insomnia and wanderlust, Kou Yamori is driven onto the moonlit streets every night in an aimless search for something he can’t seem to name. His nightly ritual is marked by purposeless introspection — until he meets Nazuna, who might just be a vampire! Kou’s new companion could offer him dark gifts and a vampire’s immortality. But there are conditions that must be met before Kou can sink his teeth into vampirism, and he’ll have to discover just how far he’s willing to go to satisfy his desires before he can heed the Call of the Night!
(Source: Sentai Filmworks)
Action, Adventure, Slice of Life, Sports

Sharks don't have lungs, but they do have to breathe oxygen to survive. Instead of breathing air, though, sharks get oxygen from the water that surrounds them. So they have to move around, if they stop moving for a while, they sink into the water and die, So Sharks have to move and move constantly from birth to death. The same goes for you. If you want to survive, keep moving, then you will be the best hunter... like a shark.
(Source: Kakao, translated)

Yoon Hana finds out that her family is moving out just before the high school entrance ceremony. At first she as worried about transferring to a new school, but her bright personality prevents her from being depressed for too long. However, the first day at the new school doesn't go quiet well how she would imagine. She quickly encounters trouble with her intimidating desk mate, Lee Chang-wook! But soon Hana starts to learn that there's more to Chang-wook than meets the eye. This is the story of the sunny Hana's project to help the gloomy Chang-wook make friends!

div.span: Turbulent Adventurers are Introverted, Observant, Feeling, Prospecting and Turbulent. They tend to have open minds, approaching life, new experiences, and people with grounded warmth.
Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Likely pragmatic and down-to-earth, with a strong focus on what is happening or very likely to happen.
Likely values emotional expression and sensitivity, prioritizing empathy, social harmony, and cooperation.
Likely very good at improvising and adapting. Tends to be flexible and values novelty above stability.
Likely self-conscious, sensitive to stress, success-driven, perfectionistic, and eager to improve.
